/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_35.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as already it was great among many another tribe,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_353.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|His name does not matter, for he plays no part in this story.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_356.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which he was transporting to Pretoria.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_358.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The weather was cold and there was little or no grass for the oxen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_362.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which made the journey difficult;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_364.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but he had been tempted to it by the high rates of transport that prevailed at that season of the year,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_369.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|which would remunerate him for any probable loss he might suffer in cattle.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_373.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So he pushed along on his journey,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_376.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and all went well until he had passed the little town of Stanger,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_38.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the royal salute,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_380.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The night after he left Stanger the air turned bitterly cold,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_383.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and hid the light of the stars.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_385.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I should say that there was a heavy fall of snow coming,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_388.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the White Man to himself.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_39.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why did you do this, my father?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_390.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have often seen the sky look like that in Scotland before snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_394.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then he reflected that there had been no deep snow in Natal for years,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_398.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|every ox in its place.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_400.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He thrust his head through the curtain of the tent and looked out.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_403.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The earth was white with snow,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_405.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the air was full of it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_406.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|swept along by a cutting wind.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_408.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now he sprang up,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_409.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|huddling on his clothes and as he did so calling to the Kaffirs who slept beneath the wagons.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_41.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will answer, who know the truth.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_415.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently they awoke from the stupor which already was beginning to overcome them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_419.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and crept out,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_421.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to them in Zulu;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_422.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Would you see the cattle die of the snow and wind?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_425.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they will give them some shelter.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_427.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And lighting a lantern he sprang out into the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_43.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You did it because,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_430.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|At last it was done-no easy task,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_432.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the White Man crept back to his bed,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_434.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the shivering natives,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_436.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|took refuge on the second wagon,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_438.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|drawing a tent-sail over them.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_440.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|save for the moaning of the huddled and restless cattle.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_443.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"If the snow goes on I shall lose my oxen,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_445.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to himself;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_446.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they can never bear this cold.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_448.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Hardly had the words passed his lips when the wagon shook;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_45.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|had it not been done,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_452.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Once more he looked out.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_453.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|running away into the night and the snow,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_455.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|seeking to find shelter from the cold.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_458.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In a minute they had vanished utterly.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_46.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps it had been better to leave it, since
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_460.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There was nothing to be done, except wait for the morning.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_463.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Such search as could be made told them nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_466.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The oxen had gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_467.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What was to be done?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_468.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he asked.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_469.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|One said this thing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_470.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but all agreed that they must wait to act until the snow melted.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_475.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Or till we freeze, you whose mothers were fools!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_478.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the White Man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_479.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was in the worst of tempers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_481.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He was the driver of the first wagon.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_483.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"My father,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_484.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to the White Man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_485.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|this is my word.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_487.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The oxen are lost in the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|No man knows whither they have gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_49.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Death chooses for himself,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or whether they live or are now but hides and bones.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_493.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he pointed to some huts about two miles away on the hillside,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_497.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the White Man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_498.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Before him was a very ancient man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_5.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his servant,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_500.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a mere bag of bones,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_501.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with sightless eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and one hand-his left-white and shrivelled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_506.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asked the old man in a thin voice.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_508.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet I will do it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_509.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though it is against your law,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_51.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and after all there was killing-of our own people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_511.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and you do wrong to ask me,-yes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_514.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will help you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_515.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My father, I know what you seek.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_517.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You seek to know where your oxen have run for shelter from the cold!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_521.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It is so, Doctor,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the White Man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_523.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You have long ears.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_525.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have long ears,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though they say that I grow deaf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_528.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have keen eyes also, and yet I cannot see your face.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_532.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let me hearken!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_534.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let me look!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You have a farm, White Man, down near Pine Town, is it not?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_539.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you shall find your oxen-yes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_54.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But in those days we did not guess what we should live to see,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_541.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the little red Zulu ox with one horn,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_544.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You shall not find these, for they have died in the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_548.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Send, and you will find the others.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I ask no fee!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_551.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I do not work wonders for reward.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the White Man scoffed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_555.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But in the end, so great is the power of superstition, he sent.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_559.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|those whom he sent returned with the oxen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_561.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|except the three only.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_563.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|After that he scoffed no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_565.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and every afternoon he came and talked with him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_568.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sitting far into the night.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_569.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|of whom he had let fall some words.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_57.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it will be forgotten,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_572.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the old man told him the tale that is set out here.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_575.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Day by day he told some of it till it was finished.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_578.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is not all written in these pages,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_58.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Only your name will not be forgotten;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_580.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Was the death of a warrior in question,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_583.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he stabbed with his stick,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_584.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|showing how the blow fell and where;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_586.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|did the story grow sorrowful, he groaned, or even wept.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_590.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Moreover, he had many voices, one for each of the actors in his tale.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_595.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This man, ancient and withered, seemed to live again in the far past.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_599.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was the past that spoke to his listener,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_6.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who slew him with the Princes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_60.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as it was heard in life so it shall be heard in story,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_602.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|telling of deeds long forgotten,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_604.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|of deeds that are no more known.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_606.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet as he best may,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_607.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and in many ways,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_608.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he has done more,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_610.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he has printed it that others may judge of it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_612.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And now his part is played.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_614.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but who had another name,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_616.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|take up the story.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_617.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the most beautiful of Zulu women.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_619.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but you are here for many nights,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_621.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it shall be told.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_622.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I have much to say that is sorrowful,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_625.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Do you know who I am, my father?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_627.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You do not know.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_628.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So men have thought for many years, but that is not my name.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_632.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Few have known it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_634.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I have kept it locked in my breast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_636.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Look at this hand, my father-no, not that which is withered with fire;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_64.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|however humbly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_641.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You see it, though I who am blind cannot.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_643.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But still, within me, I see it as it was once.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_646.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I see it red and strong-red with the blood of two kings.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_65.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|mine may pass down with it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_650.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Listen, my father; bend your ear to me and listen.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_654.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I felt you start;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_655.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he died on the Ghost Mountain;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_657.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I also was on the Ghost Mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_659.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In those days my feet still could travel fast,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_663.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I travelled by day, and by night I found him.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_666.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Why do I tell you this?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_667.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will tell you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_668.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and because he had murdered my wives and children.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_67.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I must leave the ways of action that I love and bury myself in books,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_672.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There are great names in the story, my father.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_674.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yes, many have heard the names:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_677.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have felt the mountains shake and seen the waters quiver in their sound.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_681.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But where are they now?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_682.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I opened the gates of distance for the holders of the names.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_686.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They passed through and they are gone beyond.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_688.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I cut the strings that tied them to the world.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_691.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|They fell off!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_692.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps they are falling still,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_694.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I wish I knew the snakes that I might crush them with my heel.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_698.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yonder, beneath us, at the burying-place of kings, there is a hole.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_702.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Far away in Zululand there is a cleft upon the Ghost Mountain.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_706.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the king who died for Nada.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_708.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was far to fall and he was heavy;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_71.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the old days and friends are in my mind,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_711.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|those bones of his are broken into little pieces.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_715.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I went to see them when the vultures and the jackals had done their work.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_718.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And then I laughed three times and came here to die.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_722.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|All that is long ago, and I have not died;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_725.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|that you may repeat it to the white men if you will.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_728.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Nay, I do not know.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_729.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Very, very old.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_730.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We were not a large tribe;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_732.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|perhaps there were between two and three thousand of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_735.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but they were brave.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_737.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now they are all dead,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_738.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and their women and children with them,-that people is no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_74.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|nor while I have memory shall I forget them and you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_742.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is gone like last month's moon;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_744.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Our tribe lived in a beautiful open country;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_747.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|standing as high as a man's elbow only,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_749.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother was very fond of these cows,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_752.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and there was one with a white face that would follow her about.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_755.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the boys went on with the cattle,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_757.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother sat down on the grass and nursed her baby,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_760.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and the cow grazed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_761.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|She walked like one who is tired.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_763.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|On her back was a bundle of mats,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_765.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she led by the hand a boy of about my own age,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_769.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but bigger and stronger than I was.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_77.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Elephant that is not turned!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_771.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We waited a long while,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_772.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for she was very weary.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_774.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We saw by the way her hair was dressed that she was not of our tribe.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_778.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the woman.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_779.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered my mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_780.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Food, and a hut to sleep in,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_782.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the woman.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_783.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have travelled far.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_784.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"How are you named?-and what is your people?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_787.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asked my mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_788.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the stranger.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_789.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now there had been war between our people and the Zulu people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_79.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You who nursed us from of old!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_793.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|So, when my mother heard the speech of Unandi she sprang up in anger.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_798.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|wife of a dog of a Zulu!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_799.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_8.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you have crowned their kings and shared their counsels,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_800.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was very handsome,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_801.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|waited till my mother had finished her angry words;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_804.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then she looked up and spoke slowly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_807.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said my mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_808.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We are thirsty with long travel;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_81.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You who overshadowed all peoples and took charge of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_810.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|will you not, then, give us a cup of water?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_813.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|We have found none for many hours.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_815.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will not, wife of a dog; go and seek water for yourself.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_819.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The woman's eyes filled with tears,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_821.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the boy folded his arms on his breast and scowled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_825.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He was a very handsome boy,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_827.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with bright black eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_828.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but when he scowled his eyes were like the sky before a thunderstorm.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_833.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_834.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"we are not wanted here any more than we were wanted yonder,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_837.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Yes, let us be going, my son,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_839.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered Unandi;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_840.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the path is long, we are weary and shall fall by the way.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_844.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I heard, and something pulled at my heart;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_847.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I was sorry for the woman and her boy, they looked so tired.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_85.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Help of the fatherless when in trouble!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_851.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|without saying anything to my mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_853.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for I knew that there was a spring.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_855.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Presently I came back with the gourd full of water.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_858.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother wanted to catch me,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_859.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but I ran past her and gave the gourd to the boy.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_862.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then my mother ceased trying to interfere,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_865.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|only she beat the woman with her tongue all the while,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_868.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she felt in her heart that more evil would come upon us from her son.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_87.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|PREFACE The writer of this romance has been encouraged to his task by a purpose somewhat beyond that of setting out a wild tale of savage life.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_873.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the gardens of my people would not now be a wilderness,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_876.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Unandi's son,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_877.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|having taken the gourd,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_878.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|did not offer the water to his mother.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_881.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He drank two-thirds of it himself;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_883.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I think that he would have drunk it all had not his thirst been slaked;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_887.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but when he had done he gave what was left to his mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_889.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and she finished it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_891.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and came forward,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_892.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|holding it in one hand;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_893.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|in the other he carried a short stick.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_896.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What is your name, boy?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_897.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to me as a big rich man speaks to one who is little and poor.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_902.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Mopo is my name,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_903.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I answered.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_904.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"And what is the name of your people?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_906.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Very well, Mopo; now I will tell you my name.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_909.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And I will tell you something more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_911.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But I shall grow big, so big that my head will be lost in the clouds;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_916.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you will look up and you shall not see it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_919.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My face will blind you;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_921.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it will be bright like the sun;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_923.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and my people will grow great with me;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_925.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|they shall eat up the whole world.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_927.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And when I am big and my people are big,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_930.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|then I will remember your tribe-the tribe of the Langeni,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_934.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who would not give me and my mother a cup of milk when we were weary.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_938.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You see this gourd;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_940.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|for every drop it can hold the blood of a man shall flow-the blood of one of your men.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_946.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But because you gave me the water I will spare you,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_949.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and you only,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_950.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and make you great under me.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_952.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You shall grow fat in my shadow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_954.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You alone I will never harm, however you sin against me; this I swear.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_959.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But for that woman,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_96.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When he was yet a lad,-now some seventeen years ago,-fortune took him to South Africa.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_961.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he pointed to my mother,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_963.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|let her make haste and die,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_964.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|so that I do not need to teach her what a long time death can take to come.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_969.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have spoken.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_970.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|And he ground his teeth and shook his stick towards us.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_974.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My mother stood silent awhile.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_976.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then she gasped out:
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_977.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He speaks like a man, does he?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_979.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will teach him another note-the brat of an evil prophet!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_982.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and hit her so hard on the head that she fell down.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_986.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|my father,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_987.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they were words of prophecy,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_988.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and they came true.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_990.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The last words I heard him speak were words of prophecy also,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_993.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I think that they will come true.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_995.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Even now they are coming true.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/30min/6097_997.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|In the one he told how the Zulu people should rise.
